HEADWORD: Xanthinine
<hw>Xan"thi*nine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>xanqo`s</grk> yellow + qu<ets>inine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A complex nitrogenous substance related to urea
and uric acid, produced as a white powder; -- so called because it forms
yellow salts, and because its solution forms a blue fluorescence like
quinine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xanthium</ent>⟦br⟧
